+1. vendordeps/Phoenix6.json — add Phoenix 6 2026 vendordep
+2. Constants.java — all CAN IDs, PID values, interpolation table, physical measurements
+3. subsystems/LimelightSubsystem.java — Limelight 4 via NT4, distance calc, rolling average filter
+4. subsystems/ShooterSubsystem.java — Kraken X60 via Phoenix 6, MotionMagicVelocityVoltage, 250Hz signals
+5. subsystems/HoodSubsystem.java — Falcon 500 via Phoenix 6, MotionMagicPositionVoltage, 25:1 gear ratio
+6. subsystems/DriveSubsystem.java — Pigeon 2.0 via Phoenix 6 for robot rotation
+7. commands/RotateToTargetCommand.java — PID on Limelight tx, ends within 1 degree for 0.1 seconds
+8. commands/PrepareToShootCommand.java — sets RPS and hood angle from distance interpolation table
+9. commands/WaitForShooterReadyCommand.java — waits for RPS within 1 RPS and hood within 1 degree, 2 second timeout
+10. commands/ShootCommand.java — fires only if shooter and hood are both ready
+11. RobotContainer.java — wires everything together, full shoot sequence button binding
+
+SHOOTER REQUIREMENTS:
+- Kraken X60 via TalonFX Phoenix 6 2026
+- MotionMagicVelocityVoltage for smooth consistent spin-up
+- kS, kV, kA feedforward in Constants.java
+- Target RPS from interpolation table based on Limelight distance
+- Ready when RPS within +/- 1 RPS for 0.1 seconds debounced
+- StatusSignal at 250Hz for minimal shot-to-shot variation
+- Never use open loop percent output
+
+HOOD REQUIREMENTS:
+- Falcon 500 via TalonFX Phoenix 6 2026
+- MotionMagicPositionVoltage for smooth precise movement
+- 25:1 gear ratio accounted for in sensor position conversion
+- Angle from same interpolation table as shooter RPS
+- Soft limits on TalonFX to prevent over-extension
+- Ready when within 1 degree of target
+
+LIMELIGHT REQUIREMENTS:
+- NT4 NetworkTables API, table name from Constants
+- tx, ty, tv signals
+- Distance calculated from ty, camera height, target height, camera angle
+- Rolling average of 5 distance samples to prevent jitter
+- Never use distance if tv is false
+
+AUTO-ALIGN REQUIREMENTS:
+- PID controller on Limelight tx error
+- Pigeon 2.0 for rotation stability
+- Ends when tx within 1 degree for 0.1 seconds
+- Does nothing if no valid target
+
+INTERPOLATION TABLE:
+- At least 6 distance/RPS/angle data points from 1.5m to 6m
+- Use TreeMap for automatic sorting by distance
+
+COMMENTS REQUIREMENT:
+- Every class must have a Javadoc comment explaining what it does
+- Every method must have a Javadoc comment
+- Every constant must have an inline comment with units and tuning advice
+- Every PID gain must comment: increase to X, decrease to Y
+- All non-obvious math must have step-by-step comments
+
+TUNING REQUIREMENT:
+- All tunable values in Constants.java only, never hardcoded elsewhere
+- Group Constants.java into clearly labeled sections:
+    // ── SHOOTER TUNING ──
+    // ── HOOD TUNING ──
+    // ── LIMELIGHT TUNING ──
+    // ── AUTO-ALIGN TUNING ──
+    // ── INTERPOLATION TABLE ──
+- Every tunable value must have a comment showing units and safe tuning range
+- When TUNING_MODE = true in Constants, read all PID values live from SmartDashboard
+
+RELIABILITY:
+- Never shoot if hasTarget() is false
+- Never shoot if RPM tolerance not met
+- Never shoot if hood angle tolerance not met
+- All three checks must pass simultaneously
+
+Build must pass after every single file: ./gradlew build
+TASKEOF

