+- tx, ty, tv signals
+- Distance calculated from ty, camera height, target height, camera angle
+- Rolling average of 5 distance samples to prevent jitter
+- Never use distance if tv is false
+
+AUTO-ALIGN REQUIREMENTS:
+- PID controller on Limelight tx error
+- Pigeon 2.0 for rotation stability
+- Ends when tx within 1 degree for 0.1 seconds
+- Does nothing if no valid target
+
+INTERPOLATION TABLE:
+- At least 6 distance/RPS/angle data points from 1.5m to 6m
+- Use TreeMap for automatic sorting by distance
+
+COMMENTS REQUIREMENT:
+- Every class must have a Javadoc comment explaining what it does
+- Every method must have a Javadoc comment
+- Every constant must have an inline comment with units and tuning advice
+- Every PID gain must comment: increase to X, decrease to Y
+- All non-obvious math must have step-by-step comments
+
+TUNING REQUIREMENT:
+- All tunable values in Constants.java only, never hardcoded elsewhere
+- Group Constants.java into clearly labeled sections:
+    // ── SHOOTER TUNING ──
+    // ── HOOD TUNING ──
+    // ── LIMELIGHT TUNING ──
+    // ── AUTO-ALIGN TUNING ──
+    // ── INTERPOLATION TABLE ──
+- Every tunable value must have a comment showing units and safe tuning range
+- When TUNING_MODE = true in Constants, read all PID values live from SmartDashboard
+
+RELIABILITY:
+- Never shoot if hasTarget() is false
+- Never shoot if RPM tolerance not met
+- Never shoot if hood angle tolerance not met
+- All three checks must pass simultaneously
+
+Build must pass after every single file: ./gradlew build

# 2026-03-16 00:39:15.018196
+Build a complete FRC 2026 shooter system in Java, one file at a time.
+Commit and push after each file compiles. Use Phoenix 6, WPILib 2026, NT4.
+
+HARDWARE: Kraken X60 (CAN 10) flywheel, Falcon 500 25:1 hood (CAN 11), Limelight 4, Pigeon 2.0 (CAN 20).
+
+FILES IN ORDER:
+1. vendordeps/Phoenix6.json - Phoenix 6 2025 vendordep
+2. Constants.java - all CAN IDs, PID gains, interpolation table, tuning comments
+3. subsystems/LimelightSubsystem.java - NT4, distance calc, 5-sample filter
+4. subsystems/ShooterSubsystem.java - MotionMagicVelocityVoltage, 250Hz, +/-1 RPS ready check
+5. subsystems/HoodSubsystem.java - MotionMagicPositionVoltage, 25:1 ratio, 1 degree ready check
+6. subsystems/DriveSubsystem.java - Pigeon 2.0 rotation only
+7. commands/RotateToTargetCommand.java - PID on tx, 1 degree for 0.1s debounce
+8. commands/PrepareToShootCommand.java - set RPS and hood from distance table
+9. commands/WaitForShooterReadyCommand.java - wait for both ready, 2s timeout
+10. commands/ShootCommand.java - fire only if shooter+hood+target all ready
+11. RobotContainer.java - wire everything, shoot sequence on button
+
+RULES: Javadoc every class and method. All tuning values in Constants.java with comments showing units and safe range. TUNING_MODE=true reads PID live from SmartDashboard. Never shoot without target, RPM, and hood all confirmed ready.

